theorem clopen_iff_closure_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (IsClosed (A : Set X) ∧ IsOpen (A : Set X)) ↔
      closure (A : Set X) = interior (A : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · rintro ⟨hClosed, hOpen⟩
    simpa [hClosed.closure_eq, hOpen.interior_eq]
  · intro hEq
    -- First, show that `A` is closed.
    have hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X) := by
      -- `closure A = A`.
      have h_sub : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X) := by
        simpa [hEq] using (interior_subset (s := A))
      have h_eq : closure (A : Set X) = (A : Set X) :=
        Set.Subset.antisymm h_sub subset_closure
      simpa [h_eq] using (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X)))
    -- Next, show that `A` is open.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
      -- `interior A = A`.
      have h_sub₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (A : Set X) := by
        have : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure
        simpa [hEq] using this
      have h_sub₂ : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X) :=
        interior_subset (s := A)
      have h_eq : interior (A : Set X) = (A : Set X) :=
        Set.Subset.antisymm h_sub₂ h_sub₁
      simpa [h_eq] using (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)))
    exact And.intro hClosed hOpen

theorem isOpen_of_isClosed_and_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP3 : Topology.P3 (A : Set X)) :
    IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  -- First, deduce `A ⊆ interior A` from `P3` and the fact that `closure A = A`.
  have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (A : Set X) := by
    intro x hxA
    have : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := hP3 hxA
    simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using this
  -- Since `interior A` is open and equals `A`, the set `A` is open.
  have h_eq : interior (A : Set X) = A := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact interior_subset
    · exact h_subset
  simpa [h_eq] using (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)))

theorem interior_closure_inter_interior_compl_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) ∩ interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  classical
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxIntCl, hxIntCompl⟩
    have h_mem_closure : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) :=
      interior_subset hxIntCl
    -- Using `interior (Aᶜ) = (closure A)ᶜ`
    have h_not_mem_closure : (x : X) ∈ (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
      have h_eq :=
        interior_complement_eq_complement_closure (A := A)
      simpa [h_eq] using hxIntCompl
    have hFalse : False := h_not_mem_closure h_mem_closure
    cases hFalse
  · exact Set.empty_subset _
